Dear god this film tried my patience. The alleged amazing performance from Leslie Manville as the terminally stupid Mary was lost on me. She made Brenda Blethyn in the vastly over-rated 'Secrets and Lies' seem subtle. 

I don't necessarily need a strong plot to be able to enjoy/respond to a film but I do need a point, and this film lacked any reason at all to exist. Some people in late middle-age are happy and others are completely miserable? What insight!

I put this film squarely in the Mike Leigh dustbin along with 'All or Nothing' and 'Secrets and Lies'. It does not belong up there with 'Naked', 'Life is Sweet' or 'Happy-go-Lucky' - all masterful, multi-layered films with an excess of emotional resonance. Watch those instead, not this exercise in pointlessness.
